race.comment: Can SOMEWHERE (12) land anywhere? Never in the hunt first up and then back again and too much to do last time. Draw is much the same but surely now hard fit and third up they look to play him. He's got the talent win races like this one. HIYAAM PROUD (5) recaptured her best form last time and she might go on with early promise now. Had her pegged for a bit better than this after five starts and she has hardly thrown it all away after 14. OPENING ADDRESS (1) has done his best work in patches. Had one of those patches last time, winning well, and a repeat would be a match for just about all of these. RESET THE JAZZ (2) might be one to turn things around quickly. Dropped out last time but has been back and won a jump out at Flemington and the best of him is capable.
